From: Hermes Workflow <kernel@local>
Date: Sun, 8 Jun 2026 12:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] kmi: provide sched_assist deps to unblock zram/hybridswap chain

ROOT CAUSE (verified against the stock firmware dump modules.dep):

  oplus_bsp_zram_opt.ko        depends on oplus_bsp_sched_assist.ko
  oplus_bsp_hybridswap_zram.ko depends on oplus_bsp_sched_assist.ko

oplus_bsp_sched_assist.ko fails to load on the WildKernels GKI 6.1
build with six "Unknown symbol" errors (err -2). Because the zram and
hybridswap modules list sched_assist as a hard dependency, modprobe
never even attempts them once sched_assist fails -> /dev/block/zram0
and /sys/block/zram0/hybridswap_meminfo never appear, zram + hybridswap
+ RAM expansion are all dead. This is the real blocker; patch 0003
(throttle_direct_reclaim_bypass) fixed a module that was NOT on the
zram dependency chain.

The six missing symbols fall into two classes:

1) Plain GPL exports that EXIST in the GKI source but are not exported:
     css_task_iter_start  (kernel/cgroup/cgroup.c)
     css_task_iter_next   (kernel/cgroup/cgroup.c)
     css_task_iter_end    (kernel/cgroup/cgroup.c)
     cpu_cgrp_subsys      (kernel/sched/core.c)
   -> add EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL after each definition.

2) Vendor hooks that OPLUS added to its own vmlinux but are absent from
   the WildKernels GKI:
     android_vh_reweight_entity
     android_vh_sched_move_task
   -> declare them in include/trace/hooks/sched.h. This emits the
   __tracepoint_/__traceiter_/__SCK__tp_func_ symbols the module needs
   to resolve register_trace_android_vh_*(). The hooks have no call
   sites in GKI, so the probe sched_assist registers simply never fires
   (the UX-boost reweight tweak becomes a no-op) -- but the MODULE
   LOADS, which is all that is required to unblock its zram/hybridswap
   dependents. CRC/vermagic is already neutralised by patch 0002, so
   only symbol existence matters here; signatures are taken from the
   ACK android14-6.1 vendor-hook convention (task_struct pointer for
   sched_move_task; the reweight callback was confirmed by disassembly
   to take a single sched_entity pointer in x1).

After this patch sched_assist resolves all 167 of its imports, loads,
and modprobe proceeds to oplus_bsp_zram_opt.ko and
oplus_bsp_hybridswap_zram.ko.

---
--- a/kernel/cgroup/cgroup.c
+++ b/kernel/cgroup/cgroup.c
@@ -4992,6 +4992,7 @@ void css_task_iter_start(struct cgroup_subsys_state *css, unsigned int flags,
 
 	spin_unlock_irq(&css_set_lock);
 }
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(css_task_iter_start);
 
 /**
  * css_task_iter_next - return the next task for the iterator
@@ -5025,6 +5026,7 @@ struct task_struct *css_task_iter_next(struct css_task_iter *it)
 
 	return it->cur_task;
 }
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(css_task_iter_next);
 
 /**
  * css_task_iter_end - finish task iteration
@@ -5047,6 +5049,7 @@ void css_task_iter_end(struct css_task_iter *it)
 	if (it->cur_task)
 		put_task_struct(it->cur_task);
 }
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(css_task_iter_end);
 
 static void cgroup_procs_release(struct kernfs_open_file *of)
 {
--- a/kernel/sched/core.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/core.c
@@ -11766,6 +11766,7 @@ struct cgroup_subsys cpu_cgrp_subsys = {
 	.early_init	= true,
 	.threaded	= true,
 };
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(cpu_cgrp_subsys);
 
 #endif	/* CONFIG_CGROUP_SCHED */
 
--- a/include/trace/hooks/sched.h
+++ b/include/trace/hooks/sched.h
@@ -465,6 +465,14 @@ DECLARE_HOOK(android_vh_set_task_comm,
 	TP_PROTO(struct task_struct *p),
 	TP_ARGS(p));
 
+DECLARE_HOOK(android_vh_reweight_entity,
+	TP_PROTO(struct sched_entity *se),
+	TP_ARGS(se));
+
+DECLARE_HOOK(android_vh_sched_move_task,
+	TP_PROTO(struct task_struct *tsk),
+	TP_ARGS(tsk));
+
 #endif /* _TRACE_HOOK_SCHED_H */
--- a/kernel/sched/vendor_hooks.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/vendor_hooks.c
@@ -117,3 +117,5 @@ EXPORT_TRACEPOINT_SYMBOL_GPL(android_vh_prio_restore);
 EXPORT_TRACEPOINT_SYMBOL_GPL(android_vh_task_ux_op);
 EXPORT_TRACEPOINT_SYMBOL_GPL(android_vh_set_task_comm);
+EXPORT_TRACEPOINT_SYMBOL_GPL(android_vh_reweight_entity);
+EXPORT_TRACEPOINT_SYMBOL_GPL(android_vh_sched_move_task);
